# Transformation Graph

Not knowledge graph. Not social graph.

```txt
Goals → Outcomes → Domains → Paths → Projects → Communities → Mentors → Results
```

## Moat

Not AI · not content · not courses · not communities alone.

## Pass Gate (PASS-009)

> Can Foundry observe, support, measure, and remember the transformation?

## PASS-010 Pass Gate

> Can the system identify the next highest-value action for a person trying to become something?

Content is a **byproduct** of the graph — not the center.

## PASS-010 Deliverables

Graph Query Engine · Relationship Weighting (Transformation Impact) · Transformation Analytics · Transformation Velocity · **Transformation Momentum Engine** · **Reflection Engine** · **Next Highest-Value Action Engine**

## Agency Principle

Foundry optimizes for **agency** — not knowledge, mastery, or completion.

> Can this person take meaningful action?

Knowledge ≠ Transformation. Weight toward **Transformation Impact**, not content consumption.

## PASS-010 Pass Gate

> Can the system identify the next highest-value action for a person trying to become something?

Then: **What did you learn?** · **Why is that the next best step?** · **Did it help?**

## PASS-010 Demonstration Goal

> Can we guide one person through one complete transformation cycle?

Not: Can we query the graph?

